{
  "stem": "9538.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We didn't know anything-- we had heard that the synagogues in Berlin were burning, and I had a telegram from my mother, 'come home as soon as possible.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Father has been arrested, and the synagogue has been burned down.'",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I was [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] 16 at the time.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes, 16.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I turned 16 on the 14th of November, and this was the 9th, so I would have been 16.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I came home, and my mother and all the Jewish women were in a terrible state.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "All their husbands had been arrested and been sent to Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Whereas [?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Lingen, ?] in my hometown, they did it very discreetly.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The police were ashamed, as they knew the Jewish inhabitants for so many years and lived on good terms with them.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Suddenly, for no reason whatsoever, they had to arrest them and send them in-- in-- in lorries to Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my father, as I said before, was a soldier in the first World War.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I had the bright idea to go to the CID, which was the equivalent of the German CID, which was in Osnabrueck.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I took his military passport, which he still had, and his medals, and I said he was a soldier in the first World War.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the Kaiser-- my father always used to say, the Kaiser told the troops, when he inspected the troops, and as my father was in one of the elite troops-- I'll say it first in German.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The Germany will be forever grateful for what you are doing for your fatherland.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I said this to the CID officer.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I said, and look what happened to my father and so many other former German soldiers of Jewish race.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
